<section>
<h1>Git</h1>
<h3>a distributed version control system</h3>
</section>

<section>
<h2>What is a Version Control system?</h2>
<p>Manual backups of incrementally different versions</p>
<p>Similar to these other approaches</p>
<ul>
	<li>history in Photoshop</li>
	<li>unlimited Undos</li>
	<li>Apple Time Capsule</li>
</ul>
</section>

<section>
<h2>Reasons to backup</h2>
<ul>
	<li>Retrieve historic work</li>
	<li>Share code</li>
	<li>Experiment</li>
	<li>Understand past changes</li>
</ul>
</section>

<section>
<h2>Code Portfolio</h2>
<p>Git is a creation of the programming superstar, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linus_Torvalds">Linus Torvalds</a>.</p>
<p><a href="https://github.com/">GitHub</a> is the most popular host of git.</p>
<p>Showcase your programming skills with the GitHub community.</p>
</section>

