<section>
<h3>The lifecycle of the status of your files</h3>
<ul>
	<li><small>Modified: you changed file(s) but have not committed.</small></li>
	<li><small>Staged: marked file(s) will go into your next commit snapshot.</small></li>
	<li><small>Committed: data is safely stored in your local repository.</small></li>
</ul>
<img src="../assets/git_basic_lifecycles.png">
<p><small><a href="http://git-scm.com/book/en/Getting-Started-Git-Basics">Git Basics</a></small></p>
